RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since August 4, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Clai ming Price $12,500. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Yards).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WAR COUNT set the early pace in the two path, maintained a comfortable cushion in the lead. SABER RUN ran on the rail throughout the race with a even pace. I'M D'CAT ran on the rail at a mediocre pace at first then rallied coming on to the stretch to overtake foes. GUITARTUITION PLZZ maintained a steady pace in the two path. MR. TIN MAN maintained a steady path dueling with SABER RUN until the beginning of the stretch where he jus ran out of gas. MR. FOUR SEVENS ran in the three path throughout the race, no desire to rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASTROLOGYSPROTEGE was sent to the lead, happily set a moderate pace, raced in the two path, willingly increased the lead with every pole, drew away in the furlong ground for an uncontested win. SKIPPA hooped at the start and was off slow, raced in the five path, was encouraged moving into the turn, improved position, shifted seven wide in the upper stretch, was asked and responded well by closing quickly, gaining ground, could not get to the winner but out finished the rest running a game second. BROOK IS GOLDEN stalked the pace from the two path, saved ground through out, improved position in the upper stretch, drew next to the second flight of horses, battled for second, was caught by a fast closing contender but ran a good third. FLASH FREDDIE was off in the middle of the field, raced in the four path, advanced at the three eights pole, stalked the front runners, drew beside the second tier of competitors and battled for second, then finished flat. CUSTOM CRESCENT vied for the lead, raced three wide, settled and stalked the leader, shifted into the five path in the upper stretch, raced in between foes in the second tier, battled but to no avail. MULETRAIN raced from off of the pace, raced two wide and madevno impact. DIAL UNCLE JOEY stalked the leader from the three path, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, was encouraged through the turn, improved ,shifted into the six path in the upper stretch, raced in between rivals then gave way. MR. BUTCH WOMBLE raced from off of the pace in the three path, saved ground through out, then tired. LIFEASWEKNOWIT was off a step slow, raced off of the pace and never got involved.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Yards).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDER ROAD was off a bit slow, settled off of the pace, raced in the two path, made one run, saved ground, shifted into the six path near the quarter pole, was given the cue and responded by draw away for an impressive win. FABLED RULER raced from off of the pace, raced in the three path, settled, mase one run, shifted into the six path and circled the field through the turn, was asked and responded well closing in the stretch, hooked an inside competitor in the furlong ground, battled, prevailed, out finishing the rest. NINEJUANJUAN CALL raced from off of the pace, was allowed to settle, raced in the four and five paths, found his stride around the seven sixteenth pole, shifted into he three path and saved ground, split horses in the upper stretch, closed well, just missed for second. BIG STORY went five wide in the first turn, stalked the early leader on the outside, drew near the leaders going into the second turn, challenged for and took the lead at the five sixteenth pole, was caught by an outside foe and was second by the quarter pole, raced willingly into the stretch, was caught by two fast closing rivals and gave way. PRINCE OF GLORY stalked the front runners, rated in hands, raced three wide, steadily faded after the five sixteenth pole. FETCHS BRAHM raced in the two path, laid off of the speed, stalked around the bend, shifted into the five path, at the quarter pole, maintained that position the rest of the race. LITTLE JONY vied for the lead, raced in the two and three paths, set the pace while being pressured, then stopped by the quarter pole. WESTERN STAR vied for the lead, raced in the three and four paths, co led down the back side, raced in between rivals, gave way at the three eighths pole. POINT BLANK was mid pack and raced in the six path on the outside, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, then tired entering the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALEXAPLAYBORNTORUN ran in the three path gate to wire in the lead then comfortable separated coming down the stretch. CAJUN ACES ran in the two path then rallied about half way down the stretch to make the podium. SARA'S SAPPHIRE made up the distance by running on the rail to secure a podium finish. MISS CHARLIE GRAS ran off pace of ALEXAPLAYBORNTORUN then took the turn in the four path and ended up losing speed at the sixteenth pole. HEY MADALYN CLAIRE ran in the three path but had no kick. CUSTOM GUITAR ran in the two path but didn't really have any interest in running. THE MISSING PIECE ran in the three path didn't make a move to be of any kind of threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 37. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at one mile and seventy yards).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KATIES FACTOR was forwardly placed, stalked from the three path, raced in between rivals, drew next to the early pace setter at the five sixteenth pole, matched strides until the quarter pole, battled with this rival in the upper stretch, took command after the eighth pole and drew off at the sixteenth pole winning by a nice margin. TAPS MISTRESS vied for the lead, raced in the two path, took the lead, set the early fractions while under pressure, matched strides after the five sixteenth pole, battled from the three sixteenth until the after the eighth pole, could not sustain the bid but was able to hang on for second. STORM GHOST vied for the lead, briefly led while racing five wide, settled into a stalking position, was encouraged through the turn but did not have enough for the win, but still ran well enough for third place money. CORA'S LEGACY stalked the pace from the two path, shifted into the six path in the upper stretch, could not improve position anymore down the lane. LET'S TALK DIRTY was off in the middle of the field, angled into the five path and circled the field through the turn, shifted into the three path in the upper stretch, was asked to close but struggled to switch leads and made no progress. FRONT AND SILVER broke inward, was corrected, raced mid pack, but never made an impact. EMILYHASHERTURN had the rival on the outside stumble, saw that and broke inward, was corrected, found his stride, but never got involved. SAUCY SIX was off a bit slow, made a mild gain late. TIZ MEDAGLIA was forced to check at the start, trailed. KOLLYNS JULIE stumbled badly at the start, recovered, then maintained position. GIGI'S LUV stalked the leader from the three path, shuffled back. SIBERIANA was racing mid pack in the two path faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HULEN co led while being rated, challenged for the lead after the five sixteenth pole, drew ahead by the quarter pole, was in front by a half length, was challenged in the upper stretch, was encouraged and pushed, continued to draw off for a marginal win. BAYOU BEAUX stalked the front runners from the three path, challenged for the lead at the three sixteenth pole, battled into the furlong grounds did not have enough to win but was able to secure third place. BIBLEMAN vied for the lead, co led from the two path, matched strides until after the five sixteenth pole, saved ground through ground the turn, was on even ground with the eventual winner at the three sixteenth pole, tried to battled on but gave way before the next pole. PARLAY PETE raced from mid pack, stayed on the inside and maintained position through out. OJITOS raced from mid pack, raced in the four path, launched a bid at the three eighths pole but had no kick. FIFTEEN LOVE BACK trailed through out. WONDER RUN was off a bit slow, raced in the five path, found his best stride late.
